data.title: 2017 Overwatch League BlizzCon Panel
data.description: Watch the 2017 Overwatch League BlizzCon Panel

data.title: Overwatch League: The Path to Glory
data.description: In 2017, esports will change forever. We're creating the world's premier esports ecosystem, and it all starts with you. The Overwatch League will turn distinguished amateurs into superstar athletes and give fans from every corner of the globe a professional team to root for. Here’s it how it works!

data.title: From the Overwatch League Office | Welcome Our Initial Seven Teams
data.description: It’s with great pleasure that we announce the first seven city-based teams entering the Overwatch League.

data.title: Overwatch League update:  Initial franchise announcement
data.description: Overwatch League Update - 7 Cities Announced - Nate Nanzer Interview!

data.title: Reigning Over ATL
data.description: Back in Blizzard Arena for the first time since the Atlanta Homestand, the Atlanta Reign’s Dogman and Babybay recount what it was like playing for the home crowd and how they were given a proper “Down South” welcome.

data.title: 1v1 with EQO and Sinatraa
data.description: With damage dealers popping off in Stage 4, we brought in two of the best damage players, EQO and Sinatraa, to sit down and talk about what they’re excited about and who they have their eyes on as they move towards playoffs.

data.title: Toronto Defiant RoKy and Aid Do Yoga: Access Granted
data.description: Malik Forté swings by the Toronto Defiant house to pick up RoKy and Aid for an afternoon of yoga with a special instructor. One of these players is a master of dance and the other is a Ping Pong monster. Find out which is which in this episode of Access Granted presented by Toyota.

data.title: 20(-ish) Questions with Space and KSF
data.description: The desk crew said they wanted a day off so rather than interviewing Space and KSF of the Los Angeles Valiant themselves, we decided to have them interview each other! (Also, we only had time to show you about 7 questions, not all 20. Please feel free to point this out in the comments.)

data.title: Watchpoint Game Night Part 2
data.description: In the finale of Watchpoint Game night, some of the league’s best players make their attempt to comeback vs the on-air talent.

data.title: Houston Outlaws Rawkus and coolmatt Go to the Salon: Access Granted
data.description: Rawkus and coolmatt of the Houston Outlaws join Chris Puckett on a trip to the hair salon. Get some pro tips on your style from the two best heads of hair in the Overwatch League in this episode of Access Granted presented by Toyota.
